  "texts": [
    "However, the given scheme is completely defended on client feedback, so any malicious client can send several contents for verification to launch a DoS attack.",
    "Furthermore, the mathematical correctness of the proposed scheme is mathematically incorrect.",
    "Jiancong et al. (2022) propose a dynamic content forwarding scheme for NDN to prevent CPA attacks in NDN.",
    "The authors use a public key with interest and then a digital signature on content for data and content verification.",
    "The authors also use the trust-based model to identify malicious NDN routers and bypass their routing."
